      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAJOR CRUNCH (5) is going well with two wins and two seconds from four starts this campaign. Kept the ball rolling last time when he came from the back row and scored at this circuit and distance, getting home by 1.7 metres. Stepping up a level this time but can continue the strong form. SWEET DIOR NZ (1) drew wide last start but produced a strong effort, racing parked but boxing on into third. That made it back-to-back placings from tough draws since coming from this barrier for a fresh win. Should enjoy an economical run so that gives her every chance. GREAT ACHIEVER (9) hasn't been far away of late so is on the radar. MOOPS (2) was beaten only 4.3m last week and should get his chance from another favourable draw.",
